#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:10
msgid ""
"DESCRIPTION:\tThis is a guide that will show you how to remaster LFS "
"liveCD-x86-6.2-x"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:12
msgid "PREREQUISITES:\tLFS LiveCD 6.2-x."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:16
msgid ""
"For LFS LiveCD 6.1-x, see the old \"lfscd-remastering-howto-6.1.txt\" hint "
"by Sylvie Migneault. For LFS LiveCD 6.1.1-x, the old hint should work if one "
"globally replaces LFS_CD with lfslivecd-VERSION, e.g. lfslivecd-x86-6.1.1-3"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:18
msgid "HINT:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:20
msgid "You will need:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: ' * '
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:23
msgid "Any Linux system with loop device, CD-ROM and ISO9660 filesystem support."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: ' * '
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:23
msgid "3 GB of free hard disk space on one partition."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:27
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This hint uses the $WORK environment variable as a name of a directory on "
"that\n"
"partition. E.g.:\n"
"\texport WORK=/mnt/lfslivecd\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:30
msgid ""
"The LiveCD uses the ISO9660 filesystem with Linux-specific transparent "
"decompression extension. On that filesystem, there are the following files:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:33
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tboot/*\n"
"\troot.ext2\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:36
msgid ""
"The boot directory contains the Linux kernel, the initramfs image and the "
"bootloader. The actual root filesystem (ext2) is in the root.ext2 file."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:38
msgid "In order to remaster the CD, you have to install the following packages:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:41
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"cdrtools-2.01:\n"
"\tsee the BLFS book\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:45
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"zisofs-tools-1.0.6:\n"
"\tDownload from http://www.kernel.org/pub/linux/utils/fs/zisofs/\n"
"\tBuild with ./configure --prefix=/usr && make && make install\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:48
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Mount the CD:\n"
"\tmount /media/cdrom\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:51
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Look at the root.ext2 file size:\n"
"\tls -l /media/cdrom/root.ext2\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:55
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If it is approximately 1.5 GB, the kernel uncompresses the CD for you. In\n"
"this case, you can copy the file to your hard disk as usual:\n"
"\tcp /media/cdrom/root.ext2 $WORK/root.ext2\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:59
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If it is only 500 MB, you have to rebuild your kernel with ZISOFS support, "
"or\n"
"uncompress this file manually:\n"
"\tmkzftree -u -F /media/cdrom/root.ext2 $WORK/root.ext2\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:61
msgid ""
"In either case, you end up with a $WORK/root.ext2 file that is 1.5 GB in "
"size."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:66
msgid ""
"This may or may not be sufficient for your remastered CD (or DVD) "
"filesystem.  If you want, you can resize the file with the resize2fs program "
"from e2fsprogs version >= 1.39. Earlier versions of e2fsprogs cannot resize "
"filesystem images directly."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:68
msgid "Mounting the filesystem image is achieved with a loop device:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:71
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tmkdir $WORK/root\n"
"\tmount -o loop $WORK/root.ext2 $WORK/root\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:74
msgid ""
"It is a good idea to create and bind-mount a temporary directory, in order "
"to preserve as many zeroed sectors as possible:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:77
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\tmkdir $WORK/build $WORK/root/build\n"
"\tmount --bind $WORK/build $WORK/root/build\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:83
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Mount other directories necessary for chrooting:\n"
"\tmount -t proc proc $WORK/root/proc\n"
"\tmount -t sysfs sysfs $WORK/root/sys\n"
"\tmount -t devpts devpts $WORK/root/dev/pts\n"
"\tmount -t tmpfs tmpfs $WORK/root/dev/shm\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:87
msgid ""
"Note: contrary to the instructions in the LFS book, tmpfs is not mounted on "
"$WORK/root/dev. This is because all the necessary devices are already "
"created as static nodes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:90
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Chroot to the filesystem:\n"
"\tchroot $WORK/root\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:93
msgid ""
"In the chroot, change the current directory to /build, and install any "
"additional packages you want. Modify other files as necessary."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:96
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Get the initramfs files as a zip archive from\n"
"\thttp://wiki.linuxfromscratch.org/livecd/browser/tags/6.2-3/packages/initramfs\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:100
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Unzip the archive. Remove the \"include $(ROOT)/scripts/functions\" line "
"from the\n"
"Makefile. Generate the initramfs image for your CD:\n"
"\tmake compile-stage2 VERSION=\"x86-6.2-custom\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:105
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(you can replace the \"x86-6.2-custom\" with your own string). This produces "
"the\n"
"initramfs_data.cpio.gz file in the current directory. If this directory is "
"not\n"
"\"/build\", copy it to /build:\n"
"\tcp initramfs_data.cpio.gz /build\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:114
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Exit from the chroot and clean up the mounts:\n"
"\texit\n"
"\tumount $WORK/root/dev/shm\n"
"\tumount $WORK/root/dev/pts\n"
"\tumount $WORK/root/sys\n"
"\tumount $WORK/root/proc\n"
"\tumount $WORK/root/build\n"
"\trmdir $WORK/root/build\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:117
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Clean up bash history:\n"
"\trm $WORK/root/root/.bash_history\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:119
msgid "You may also want to remove other history files."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:124
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"If you, by mistake, created and removed some files, the sectors previously\n"
"occupied by those files begin to contain non-zero data. Such sectors are\n"
"useless, but they don't compress well. Zero them out:\n"
"\tdd if=/dev/zero of=$WORK/root/zeroes\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:128
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This command will print a message that the disk is full. This is not an "
"error.\n"
"Then, remove the file that fills the filesystem:\n"
"\trm $WORK/root/zeroes\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:132
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now you can unmount the root.ext2 file:\n"
"\tumount $WORK/root\n"
"\tsync\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:135
msgid ""
"The \"sync\" command is needed due to a bug in the loop driver in some "
"kernels that leads to a filesystem with errors otherwise."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:138
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Now make the directory structure for your LiveCD:\n"
"\tmkdir $WORK/iso\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:141
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Copy the boot directory from the original LiveCD:\n"
"\tcp -r /media/cdrom/boot $WORK/iso\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:145
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Replace the stock initramfs image with your own:\n"
"\tcp $WORK/build/initramfs_data.cpio.gz \\\n"
"\t    $WORK/iso/boot/isolinux/iniramfs_data_cpio.gz\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:147
msgid "(the underscore before \"cpio\" in the previous command is not a typo)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:150
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Recompress the root.ext2 file:\n"
"\tmkzftree -F $WORK/root.ext2 $WORK/iso/root.ext2\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/lfscd-remastering-howto-6.2.txt:156
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Recreate the CD image:\n"
"\tcd $WORK/iso ; mkisofs -z -R -l --allow-leading-dots -D -o \\\n"
"        ../lfslivecd-x86-6.2-custom.iso -b boot/isolinux/isolinux.bin \\\n"
"        -c boot/boot.cat -no-emul-boot -boot-load-size 4 -boot-info-table "
"\\\n"
"        -V \"lfslivecd-x86-6.2-custom\" ./\n"
msgstr ""

